ce:section.ce:para:
The peroxidase-like property of the Janus micro-composite was determined by colorimetric detection, and TMB was selected as the chromogenic substrate. Specifically, 0.1 mg/mL Janus micro-composite (50 μL), 100 μL of 0.2 M H2O2 solution and 200 μL of 0.25 mM TMB were added into 1.65 mL NaAc-HAc solution (pH = 6.0) and reacted for 10 min. Finally, the absorption value of the blue solution at 652 nm was measured immediately by UV absorption spectrometer. The kinetic test of H2O2 and TMB by Janus micro-composite was also obtained by Lineweaver-Burk equation. Michaelis constant (
k m
) and maximum reaction velocity (
v max
) were calculated by Lineweaver-Burk equation.
